sentences: Jon Baker (born 1960) is a music industry executive.
Born in 1960 in London, | Baker’s mother was a British fashion designer and his father sold classic cars.

In 1979, operations grew and Blooze was relocated to the Great Gear Market, Kings Road, London and renamed Axiom.

Gee Street Records, 1985–90

In 1985, Baker organized Doug E. Fresh and Slick Rick's first UK tour.
Then, in 1988, he signed the Stereo MCs to a licensing deal with Island Records.

In 1990, Chris Blackwell signed P.M. Dawn, and proposed a joint venture with Island/PolyGram that secured Gee Street's roster for Island.
In 1996, Blackwell left Island and the Polygram group.
Baker sold his shares of Gee Street to Richard Branson in 2000.
In 2002, he moved to Jamaica, became a Jamaican citizen.
